      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I strongly advise against taking more than the recommended dose of ibuprofen or any other medication, as it can be extremely dangerous and lead to serious health complications. The recommended maximum daily dose for ibuprofen is usually between 3200-3200 mg for adults, which is divided into several doses throughout the day. Taking more than this can lead to stomach ulcers, bleeding, kidney damage, and other serious issues.\n\nIt's critically important to seek medical attention, even if it's just a telehealth consultation. I understand it's late and inconvenient, but your health is too important to risk further harm with excessive medication. There are safe alternatives and pain management strategies that can help you sleep without endangering your body. Please reach out to a medical professional as soon as possible.",
